        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 3:07AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 306 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Champion to 12 miles
southeast of Forsan. Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Colorado City, Loraine, Forsan, Colorado City Airport, Lake Colorado
City, Champion Creek Reservoir, Lake Colorado City State Park,
Westbrook, and Buford.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 202 and 228.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
